 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Information Security Compliance Analyst II Buoy Health New York, NY Remote Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Mission 
We create technology, with heart, for the health of every person in the world. 
Company Overview 
Buoy builds a digital health tool that helps people – from the moment they get sick – start their health care on the right foot. Started by a team of doctors and computer scientists working at the Harvard Innovation Laboratory in Boston MA, Buoy was developed in direct response to the downward spiral we’ve all faced when we attempt to self-diagnose your symptoms online. Buoy leverages artificial intelligence – powered by advanced machine learning and proprietary granular data - to resemble an exchange you would have with your favorite doctor – to provide consumers with a real-time, accurate analysis of their symptoms and help them easily and quickly embark on the right path to getting better. Buoy is based in Boston and was founded in 2014. 
Job Description 
Buoy is taking on the multi-faceted challenge of applying Artificial Intelligence to medicine and developing novel interfaces and algorithms to reason about the relationship between humans, symptoms, and illnesses. We are looking for an Information Security Compliance Analyst II to join a collaborative cross-functional team dedicated to helping the business adhere to information security policies, obtain and maintain compliance certifications, and expand our security and compliance programs. The ideal candidate will have a passion for the compliance aspects of information security, a strong desire to grow and expand their security knowledge, and will excel at communicating with both technical and non-technical members of the organization. 
 
 **This role is located in the United States. Unfortunately, we are unable to support international applicants at this time. 
 Responsibilities 
Develop, review and update information security policies & procedures 
Conduct reviews of user access and other periodic activities defined by our security framework 
Assist with the continued compliance of HITRUST certification 
Develop and present materials related to security awareness training 
Perform due diligence of new and existing third-party vendors 
Establish systems and processes for managing organizational risks as they relate to information security 
Assist with prioritizing, tracking, and reporting on security vulnerability and compliance issue remediation 
Create and package collateral to help prospective customers review Buoy’s security programs 
 Minimum Qualifications 
2+ years work experience in information security, compliance, or audit roles 
Strong understanding of information security frameworks such as NIST, ISO, CIS, SOC, and HIPAA, particularly in the context of the public cloud 
Experience evaluating information systems with a lens for security issues 
Ability to understand complex technical system architectures 
Experience maintaining information security policy documents 
Experience developing programs to manage organizational risk 
Proficiency with business software applications such as Google G Suite and Atlassian Jira 
Ability to cater communications to both technical and non-technical audiences 
 Preferred Qualifications 
Previous experience working in highly regulated industries such as healthcare or finance 
Experience utilizing Cloud Security Posture Management and Workload Protection systems such as AWS Security Hub, Palo Alto Prisma Cloud, or Twistlock to identify and remediate security issues 
Familiarity with Open Source Software licensing and usage compliance 
Experience with the intricacies of securing macOS and Amazon Linux operating systems 
Exposure to enterprise security programs such as vendor due diligence, change management, product governance, and risk management 
Previous experience securing public cloud resources in AWS or GCP 
A knack for designing processes that are both scalable and sustainable 
 Company Benefits 
Stock Options 
